    <p><b>Meteor Capture</b></p>

<p>A meteor of mass \(m\) is approaching earth as shown in the sketch. The radius of the earth 
is \(R_e\) and the mass of the earth is \(M\).  Suppose the meteor has an initial speed of \(v_0\) and 
starts very far away from the earth. You may ignore all other gravitational forces except the earth. 
Find the impact parameter \(h\) for the case when the meteor just grazes the Earth: </p>

